pageContext.claim: “You remember the previous administration? ‘We can't create manufacturing jobs anymore.’”
pageContext.analysis: Trump frequently says President Obama once told an audience that the U.S. would not be able to recover lost manufacturing jobs. Obama never said this. At a town hall in 2016, he said more manufacturing jobs had been created during his term than at any time since the 1990s, adding that some manufacturing jobs could be recovered and some have disappeared because of automation and other economic trends.
